com.engineersbox.httpproxy.connection.stream

Class StreamCollector<T extends HTTPStartLine>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.engineersbox.httpproxy.connection.stream.StreamCollector<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - An implementation of abstract class HTTPStartLine
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ContentCollector<T>

    public class StreamCollector<T extends HTTPStartLine>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ContentCollector<T>
    Socket stream reader used to construct HTTP messages received via a bound Socket's InputStream, on a per-request basis. Messages are read and constructed according to RFC 2616.

    Note that this reader supports automatic decompression of the following formats, done after having identified the Content-Type header
    • GZIP: Lempel-Ziv coding (LZ77) with a 32 bit CRC (RFC 1952).
    • compress: Adaptive Lempel-Ziv-Welch coding (LZW) (RFC 7230)
    • deflate: zlib format (RFC 1950) with deflate compression mechanism (RFC 1951).
    • zstd: ZStandard compression standard (RFC 8478)
    • br: Brotli compression standard (RFC 7932)
